<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2852] Infinite reloading of config file ending with .config</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2852</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a config file ending with .config is written back to the file system, lastModified is updated even if the file has not changed since it was last written/read. Config files ending with .cfg are not affected by this as lastModified is not updated if the file has not changed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Workaround: apply the patch from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2843&quot; title=&quot;Parsing PID assumes last 4 chars are file extension&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FELIX-2843&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FELIX-2843&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and set felix.fileinstall.disableConfigSave=false&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12499270">FELIX-2852</key>
            <summary>Infinite reloading of config file ending with .config</summary>
