                        <due></due>
                            <votes>3</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12997539" author="thecarlhall" created="Mon, 21 Feb 2011 19:31:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a preliminary patch put together to update the .config file&apos;s checksum in the scanner but have hardcoded how the scanner is retrieved. I will continue to refine the patch and attach it once I am satisfied with it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13003836" author="thecarlhall" created="Tue, 8 Mar 2011 06:50:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached a patch to manually update a file&apos;s checksum after writing a .config file. The checksum is only updated in scanners that have prior knowledge of the file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13019170" author="thecarlhall" created="Wed, 13 Apr 2011 02:43:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bumping up to &quot;critical&quot; as infinite loops can get painful. Not a blocker as there is a workaround.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13212579" author="jstrom" created="Tue, 21 Feb 2012 13:30:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;~1 year later; is there any update on this bug? I still have this problem running 3.1.10 (as shipped with Apache Karaf 2.2.5). As 3.1.10 is the latest version released, and the workaround doesn&apos;t work on the released version, I&apos;d say this is a problem. Patching trunk manually isn&apos;t too production-friendly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
